  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>Proficient in using Revit, Navisworks, AutoCAD etc BIM/CAD software.</p><p>Manage all architectural and structural modelling, technical drawings/detailing, and documentation using BIM software.</p><p>Coordinate with all disciplines project coordinators to deliver the project.</p><p>Manage internal coordination drawing schedule and the subcontractor model updates.</p><p>Coordinate with all the parties including sub-contractors and consultants to solve and coordinate the technical issues.</p><p>Production and maintaining of drawings from BIM (Revit) model and ensure proper transmission of data to all parties involved.</p><p>Ensure that the detailed schedules of drawing production and site progress are met.</p><p>For quality management, the coordinator is responsible to fully implement with the quality recordings, carry out result analysis and formulate action plans for continuous improvement.</p><p>Well knowledge on BIM modelling, BIM implementation and BIM data transmission. .</p><p>Ensure BIM standards and Level of Development (LOD) are followed.</p><p>Ad-hoc matters as assigned by the PM which is necessary for the execution of the project.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Architecture / Engineering / Construction related fields.</li><li>BCA trained/certified BIM course will be preferred. HDB or residential project experience will be preferred.</li><li>Multi-disciplines required: Architectural, Structural and MEP:</li><li>Minimum 5 years' experience for BIM coordinator role.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
